Typography.StandardSwashes="0" Typography.ContextualSwashes="0" Typography.StylisticAlternates="0"><Paragraph><Run FontWeight="Bold" FontSize="12.75">Purpose:</Run></Paragraph><Paragraph><Run>This network is the first attempt at having Sallie move objects in her environment. There is a single red object and a single green target and it is Sallie's goal to put the red object on the goal.</Run></Paragraph><Paragraph><Run>She first experiments with the object to determine what level of action causes what level of motion. Then she follows an algorithm to move the object to the goal.</Run></Paragraph><Paragraph><Run>This is the beginning of many new experiments in goals, trial-and-error, feedback/eye-hand coordination. </Run></Paragraph><Paragraph><Run FontWeight="Bold" FontSize="12.75">Things to try:</Run></Paragraph><Paragraph><Run>First, fire the "Auto" neuron. Sallie will make three approaches to the object to learn it characteristics.</Run></Paragraph><Paragraph><Run>Second, fire the "Goal" neuron (with the Auto neuron still firing). Sallie with move the object to the goal.</Run></Paragraph><Paragraph><Run>You can set different object lengths and goal positions in the Sim module. The goal must be given a weight of 10.</Run></Paragraph><Paragraph><Run></Run></Paragraph><Paragraph><Run FontWeight="Bold" FontSize="12.75">Current state of development:</Run></Paragraph><Paragraph><Run>This is the first version of this program. Vision is not supported. Sallie doesn't learn in an AI sense but follows a few internal algorithms. Next steps are to expand these abilities.</Run></Paragraph><Paragraph><Run></Run></Paragraph><Paragraph><Run FontWeight="Bold" FontSize="12.75">Notes:</Run></Paragraph><Paragraph><Run></Run></Paragraph><Paragraph><Run></Run></Paragraph><Paragraph><Run></Run></Paragraph></Section>
